{
  "circuit": {
    "description": "Inductor-induced DC branch-current singularity: V1=3V (node 1) and V2=5V (node 2) are bridged by ideal L1=1mH. The static DC ladder is singular on l1#branch (gmin is a node-to-ground conductance and cannot constrain a branch current), so direct NR + gmin + source stepping all fail. OPtran pseudo-transient settles to the unique OP v(1)=3, v(2)=5. Adding any series R makes it converge statically, proving the inductor short is the cause.",
